      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T08:01:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 64: The RTT component treats absolute RTT as congestion instead of RTT growth/excess. With the defaults, a normal 100 ms RTT contributes 0.1 to the score, exceeding the 0.08 threshold even with zero loss, so the controller will repeatedly decrease bitrate on stable long-distance calls. Track a baseline/min RTT and score only excess delay, or raise/remove the absolute RTT contribution.\n```suggestion\n    auto rttExcess \u003d std::max(0.0f, ewmaRtt_ - baselineRtt_);\n    float rttComponent \u003d std::max(0.0f, rttExcess / cfg_.congestionRttScale);\n```",
      "revId": "c09733eed97b065abe8c73b450c0a1f9c6ba8268",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
