      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T08:01:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 130: update() accepts packetLoss, jitterMs, and rttMs without validating their ranges. RTCPInfo can contain sentinel/invalid values such as negative latency or NO_INFO-like loss, and those values are folded into the EWMA and congestion score. Clamp percentages and ignore unavailable RTT/jitter samples before updating the filters so one invalid report cannot poison the controller state.\n```suggestion\n    packetLoss \u003d std::clamp(packetLoss, 0.0f, 100.0f);\n    jitterMs \u003d std::max(0.0f, jitterMs);\n    rttMs \u003d std::max(0.0f, rttMs);\n```",
      "revId": "c09733eed97b065abe8c73b450c0a1f9c6ba8268",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
