      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T08:01:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 645: The restart grace period was removed from the loss/RTT adaptation path. The old dropProcessing() ignored RTCP samples for DELAY_AFTER_RESTART after sender start/restart to avoid reacting to stale feedback while the encoder and receiver settle. The new controller consumes RR immediately, so stale packet loss after restart can force an unnecessary bitrate drop. Keep the restart guard before feeding RR stats to the controller.\n```suggestion\n    auto now \u003d clock::now();\n    if (now - lastMediaRestart_ \u003c DELAY_AFTER_RESTART)\n        return;\n```",
      "revId": "c09733eed97b065abe8c73b450c0a1f9c6ba8268",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
