      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 657: REMB feedback now updates only the controller state and is never applied to the encoder unless an RR packet is also available in the same pass. If check_RCTP_Info_RR() returns false, overuse REMB reductions are silently dropped and setupVideoBitrateInfo() on the next iteration can resync the controller from the unchanged codec bitrate. Apply the returned bitrate immediately, or otherwise ensure REMB-only feedback reaches setNewBitrate().\n```suggestion\n        if (isOveruse || br \u003d\u003d 0x7378) {\n            auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.onRembFeedback(isOveruse);\n            setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n        }\n```",
